Chocolate Fudge Avocado Cake

INGREDIENTS
**Cake**
3 (1 1/4 cups) fresh avocados, mashed (use medium-ripe avocadoes for best results)
4 eggs
1 cup honey
1 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
1 cup almond flour
1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla 
3/4 teaspoon baking soda
1/2 teaspoon salt

**Frosting**
2 (3/4) fresh avocados
1/2 cup honey
1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
2 tablespoons coconut oil

INSTRUCTIONS
**Prepare cake**
Preheat oven to 350 F.
Blend all cake ingredients in a food processor until smooth.
Back in a spray coated 9 inch cake pan for 25-35 minutes until done.
Cool completely before adding frosting.

**Prepare the Frosting**
Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Chill at least 30 minutes before speading on the cake. 

Makes 6-8 servings.
